2 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
3 POLICY COMMITTEE
RECOMMENDATION
4 FOR
HOUSE BILL NO. 3552 By: Maynard
5
6
7 POLICY COMMITTEE RECOMMENDATION
8 An Act relating to children; authorizing childcare
providers to charge differential; prohibiting the
9 Department of Human Services from penalizing or
taking adverse action against providers; requiring
10 providers to apply differential uniformly; directing
the Department to promulgate rules; providing for
11 codification; and providing an effective date.
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 431 of Title 10, unless there is
17 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 A. Upon approval by the Administration for Children and
19 Families, a licensed or permitted childcare provider serving a child
20 eligible for the Department of Human Services' Child Care Subsidy
21 Program may charge the child's parent or legal guardian the
22 difference between:
23 1. The Department's subsidy reimbursement rate applicable to
24 the child; and
Req. No. 16583 Page 1

1 2. The provider's standard private tuition rate for the same
2 age group and schedule.
3 B. The Department shall not:
4 1. Prohibit, restrict, or penalize a provider for charging a
5 differential authorized pursuant to this act; or
6 2. Take adverse action against a provider, including, but not
7 limited to, disqualification, enhanced monitoring, subsidy
8 enrollment restrictions, or corrective action, solely due to the
9 provider charging a differential pursuant to this act.
10 C. Providers who charge a differential shall apply the
11 differential uniformly to all similarly situated families.
12 D. The Department shall promulgate rules, update subsidy
13 agreements, and provide guidance documents to comply with the
14 provisions of this act.
15 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
